		<introduction>
			<para>
				Animation frames can be rendered without or with <newTerm>image smoothing</newTerm>. The difference is subtle,
				but <newTerm>edge smoothing</newTerm> can have a particularly noticeable effect in moving animations. These options
				only apply when animation frames are rendered at their normal size. When an animation is stretched or
				shrunk, Double Agent uses <newTerm>bicubic interpolation</newTerm> to resize its frames.
			</para>
			<para>
				The table below shows examples of animation frames rendered using the smoothing options, and also at
				different sizes. You can see that a character shown at half-size or even iconic size (32 by 32 pixels)
				is still recognizable.
			</para>
		</introduction>

